# Next.js 15 Best Practices

## App Router Patterns
- Use Server Components by default — add `'use client'` only when needed (event handlers, hooks, browser APIs)
- Colocate loading.tsx, error.tsx, not-found.tsx in route segments
- Use `generateStaticParams` for all data-driven routes (suburbs, services, blog)
- Use `generateMetadata` for dynamic SEO — never hardcode meta tags

## Data Fetching
- Fetch data in Server Components, not client
- Use Supabase server client (`@supabase/ssr`) in server components
- Cache with `unstable_cache` or ISR `revalidate` — never fetch on every request
- Pass data down as props, don't refetch in children

## Performance
- Use `next/image` with explicit width/height — never `<img>`
- Use `next/font` for Roboto — never external Google Fonts links
- Lazy-load below-fold sections with `dynamic(() => import(...), { ssr: false })`
- Keep client bundles small — extract server logic into `lib/`

## File Naming
- Route files: `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`
- Components: PascalCase (`HeroSection.tsx`)
- Utilities: camelCase (`lib/schema.ts`, `lib/seo.ts`)
- No `index.tsx` barrel files — import directly

## Anti-Patterns
- Never use `useEffect` for data fetching
- Never put API keys in client components
- Never use `router.push` for SEO-critical navigation — use `<Link>`
- Never use `suppressHydrationWarning` to hide bugs
